<subSubSection pageId="498" pageNumber="499" type="diversity">
<paragraph pageId="498" pageNumber="499">Diversity.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="498" pageNumber="499">Twenty-three species (Lorenz 2005: 269), mostly in the arctic and subarctic areas, in North America (one species), Asia (21 species), and eastern Europe (three species).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="498" pageNumber="499" type="identification">
<paragraph pageId="498" pageNumber="499">Identification.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="498" pageNumber="499">No revision or identification key is available for the species. Lindroth (1966: 476-478) covered the North American species.</paragraph>
